            <p>Jewish Publication Society of America.<lb/></p>
            <p>NEW YORK&#44; Dec. 13&#44; 1888<lb/></p>
            <p>DEAR SIR&#58;<lb/></p>
            <p>We beg to enclose a blank Postal and ask you to fill<lb/> up the same either as patron or member&#44; and unite with us in the<lb/> work of securing the permanent existence of the Jewish Publication<lb/> Society of America.<lb/></p>
            <p>From the enclosed circular you will take note of its objects<lb/> and the good work it proposes to accomplish for the higher education<lb/> of American Israelites.  Already Philadelphia has come into line with<lb/> a membership roll of many hundreds&#44; and we desire to see New York<lb/> respond with similar liberality.<lb/></p>
            <p>Previous efforts in the past in this behalf have failed for<lb/> want of proper appreciation and publicity.  Our communities have<lb/> now grown so considerable&#44; the young men and women of Israel so<lb/> numerous&#44; the desire for knowledge of Jewish History and Literature<lb/> is so favorably advanced&#44; that we feel we shall not appeal for<lb/> your co&#45;operation in vain.<lb/></p>
            <p>The subject is one that addresses itself to the intelligence<lb/> of our people.  It is in no sense a charity.  We simply ask you&#44;<lb/> by becoming a contributor&#44; to invest the amount of your annual dues<lb/> in Jewish Literature of the highest standard.  Every Israelite&#44; every<lb/> intelligent citizen has a personal interest in becoming still more<lb/> enlightened&#44; and in diffusing knowledge&#44; thus elevating the character<lb/> in cultivating and developing the higher aspirations of our nature.<lb/></p>
            <p>Please favor us with an early reply.<lb/></p>
            <p>JACOB H. SCHIFF&#44;<lb/>
                Chairman N. Y. Committee.<lb/>
                BENJAMIN F. PEIXOTTO&#44; Secretary.<lb/>
                Rev. Dr. G. Gottheil&#44;<lb/>
                Rev. Dr. A Kohut&#44;		N. Y.<lb/>
                Henry M. Leipziger&#44;		Committee.<lb/></p>
            <p>Emanuel Lehman&#44;<lb/>
                Jacob H. Flesich&#44;<lb/>
                James H. Hoffman&#44;<lb/>
                Edwin R. Seligman&#44;<lb/>
                Newman Cowen&#44;		Special Committee.<lb/>
                Edward Lauterbach&#44;<lb/>
                Myer S. Isaacs&#44;<lb/>
                Adolph L. Sanger&#44;<lb/></p>
            </body>
